The distribution of the track isolation of selected candidates in data is used to discriminate between prompt and background photon candidates, before and after applying the tight identification criteria. The track isolation variable used for the measurement of the efficiency of unconverted photon candidates, pTiso\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
