The remaining difference between the corrected simulation and the data-driven measurements is taken into account by computing data-to-MC efficiency ratios, also referred to as scale factors (SF). The data-to-MC efficiency ratios are computed separately for each method and then combined. The efficiencies from the Z→ℓℓγ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
